        },
        "text": "Limitation on the Use of the Cash Method of Accounting.\u2014Except as provided below, C corporations, partnerships with a C corporation as a partner, and tax shelters may not use the cash method of accounting. For purposes of this limitation, a trust subject to the tax on unrelated business income under section 511 is treated as a C corporation with respect to its unrelated trade or business activities."
